# Branch-specific environment configuration
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is COMMITTED to git and SHARED across the team!
# These configurations coordinate with shared external dev resources.
#
# Copy this template to create your branch-specific environment:
#   cp environment/.env.branch.template environment/.env.branch.main
#   cp environment/.env.branch.template environment/.env.branch.feature-name
#
# ✅ DO commit here (shared team configuration):
#   - Shared dev resource endpoints (staging DB hostname, dev API URL)
#   - Branch-specific infrastructure names (AWS stack, k8s namespace)
#   - Feature flags for the branch
#   - Non-secret resource identifiers
#
# ❌ DON'T commit here (use .env.local instead):
#   - Passwords, API keys, tokens
#   - Machine-specific paths or ports
#   - Personal developer preferences
#   - Any secrets or credentials
#
# For personal/secret overrides, create (gitignored):
#   - .env.local (applies to all branches)
#   - environment/.env.branch.main.env.local (branch-specific secrets)

